00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:43,708
Oh, yeah, we never
decided on a name, did we?

253
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:46,333
No, we didn't, and we
can't very well keep

254
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:47,833
calling it a music club.

255
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,708
Huh? How should we
decide on one, though?

256
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:52,041
Here's kind of an idea.

257
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:54,541
What if we used all of our
names together somehow?

258
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:04,416
"Fall moon"?

259
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,208
But "aki" means
autumn, doesn't it?

260
00:12:06,291 --> 00:12:07,250
Close enough.

261
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:08,791
I think we can
change it to "fall."

262
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:12,250
Wow, I like it.

263
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:13,625
[NACHI, FUUKA, YUU]
Huh?

264
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:15,416
"Fall Moon."

265
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,958
I guess "fallen" is actually
more accurate though,

266
00:12:18,041 --> 00:12:20,708
just if we wanna be
grammatically correct.

267
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:22,500
Wow, I love that.

268
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:24,125
"The Fallen Moon" is cool!

269
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,125
Yeah, I really like how
poetic it is, ya know?

270
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:27,291
[FUUKA]
Wait!

271
00:12:27,375 --> 00:12:29,625
Using my name makes
me seem egotistical!

272
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:31,958
Like I forced this band
together, or something!

273
00:12:36,708 --> 00:12:38,708
[SARA sighs]

274
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:41,250
[NACHI]
Um, you did.

275
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,541
[MIKASA]
Yeah, that happened.

276
00:12:42,625 --> 00:12:44,458
I'd say that's pretty accurate.

277
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:49,375
Uh...

278
00:12:49,458 --> 00:12:50,708
Okay, fine, then!

279
00:12:50,791 --> 00:12:53,000
But I don't wanna hear
a word about it later on!

280
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,541
[PATRONS talking]

281
00:12:57,625 --> 00:13:01,000
That was fast, the
concert's posted already.

282
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:03,291
It has tons of views, too.

283
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:05,416
[SARA] Not surprising
after that tweet blew up.

284
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:08,208
Plus, Koyuki
showing up was huge.

285
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:10,000
[YUU]
Did you guys see?

286
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:13,208
Someone from her agency
took her away afterwards.

287
00:13:13,291 --> 00:13:15,000
Think she's okay?

288
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,583
[GROUP sighs]

289
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:19,000
Man, I hope so but,
it's hard to say.

290
00:13:19,083 --> 00:13:21,125
She's in a different
position than we are.

291
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:38,041
[YAMADA] Well, we got a
little slap on the wrist

292
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:39,333
from the president.

293
00:13:39,416 --> 00:13:41,583
He's such a nag sometimes.

294
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:44,291
I'm so sorry.
This is all my fault.

295
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:46,083
It's fine, no worries.

296
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:48,250
All I need is for
you to promise

297
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:50,000
never to act on your own again.

298
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:52,541
Can I have your word on that?

299
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:53,916
Okay.

300
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,000
And as far as the boy goes--
Haruna, was it?

301
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:59,791
It'll be best if you don't
contact him again for a while.

302
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:01,250
[KOYUKI gasps]

303
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:02,458
[YAMADA] You can never
tell what's going to

304
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:04,000
cause another big fuss.

305
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:08,416
My first priority
is to keep you safe.

306
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:09,541
'Kay.

307
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,541
Hey. You know what will
make you feel better?

308
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:17,375
Throwing yourself back into
the work that you love, right?

309
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:19,750
So, let's see.
I've got your schedule.

310
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:22,375
The agency will, of course, take
care of the press, so you don't

311
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,750
have to worry about any
of that, thank goodness.

312
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,416
And as far as your concert,

313
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:29,333
we were able to nail down
the details for rehearsals...

314
00:14:29,416 --> 00:14:34,500
[reciever ringing]

315
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:48,041
[GIRL F] The finals cover
too much material!

316
00:14:48,125 --> 00:14:49,708
[BOY A]
It was so cold this morning.

317
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,166
So, Haruna.

318
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:53,375
Have you talked to Koyuki
since the concert happened?

319
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:57,000
I've tried. But not yet.

320
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,250
That's a bummer.

321
00:14:58,333 --> 00:15:00,416
Sure is, kinda concerning.

322
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,500
[gasps]
Yuu, look at this!

323
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,166
--[YUU] Huh?
--What is it?

324
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,458
[FUUKA]
What's wrong?

325
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:08,958
[gasps]

326
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:29,541
[gasps]

327
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,125
[sighs]
Please, Tama...

328
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,833
[PRODUCER A] Okay, first,
how about we run through

329
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:02,000
"Snow Fireworks."

330
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:04,083
Great!

331
00:16:04,166 --> 00:16:06,583
[KOYUKI] This concert
is all I have left, now.

332
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:08,958
I have to make it my best ever.

333
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:15,458
[KOYUKI] I'll do it for
the ones who are out there,

334
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,041
counting on me.

335
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:23,333
♪

336
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,916
[PRODUCER A]
Anything wrong, Koyuki?

337
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,375
[KOYUKI]
No, sorry.

338
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:43,041
All right! Then once
more from the top.

339
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:48,333
♪

340
00:16:48,416 --> 00:16:50,000
[gasps, rasps]

341
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,750
[KOYUKI gasps]
My voice.

342
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:56,125
[YAMADA gasps]

343
00:17:11,458 --> 00:17:15,083
So, I've just been talking
it over with the president.

344
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:16,666
Yes?

345
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,875
[YAMADA] He feels like
we should give you

346
00:17:17,958 --> 00:17:20,208
a break from
singing for a while.

347
00:17:20,291 --> 00:17:22,291
Wait, not even the
Christmas concert?

348
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:23,416
[YAMADA]
Hmm. That's right.

349
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:26,750
But I have to! I can't just--

350
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,625
The thing is,
the doctor said this was

351
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:31,875
probably caused by stress,
so you need to take a rest.

352
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:33,583
Just a little time off.

353
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:35,916
I would never want you
to feel overworked.

354
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:38,541
[KOYUKI sighs]

355
00:17:50,416 --> 00:17:51,750
[KOYUKI]
Nico...

356
00:17:53,791 --> 00:17:55,750
[GIRL G]
Look! I scored amazing seats!

357
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:56,750
Seats for what?

358
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,958
Koyuki Hinashi's
Christmas concert!

359
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,333
[GIRL H]
Oh, that's right!

360
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:01,958
I forgot what a
huge fan you are!

361
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:03,416
[GIRL G]
Yeah, I'm freaking out!

362
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:05,291
It's insanely hard
to get tickets!

363
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,625
[KOYUKI gasps]

364
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:12,666
[YAMADA]
Sorry I'm late!

365
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:15,166
But, look, I grabbed
you a little something.

366
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:16,416
Here.

367
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:19,083
Thanks, I needed chocolate.

368
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:24,000
[phone buzzes]

369
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:28,916
[KOYUKI sighs]

370
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:39,833
[sighs]

371
00:18:39,916 --> 00:18:41,833
Get up! Have you
heard the news?

372
00:18:41,916 --> 00:18:43,666
What? No, what news?

373
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:45,125
They're saying it everywhere!

374
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:46,875
Koyuki's going on hiatus!

375
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:48,666
All her concerts
were called off--

376
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,166
they said it's her health!

377
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,291
[YUU]
Let me see.

378
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,125
So sudden. Do you think
Koyuki's gonna be okay?

379
00:19:05,208 --> 00:19:08,000
I don't know. But...

380
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:49,208
[phone buzzes

381
00:19:49,291 --> 00:19:50,208
Ah.

382
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:54,875
[buzzing continues]

383
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,333
[gasps]

384
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:03,000
[YUU] Hello?! Did you
really just answer?

385
00:20:03,083 --> 00:20:05,083
--[KOYUKI] Hi, Nico.
--[YUU] Hi.

386
00:20:05,166 --> 00:20:07,333
I've been worried since I
couldn't seem to reach you.

387
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,625
Is everything okay?

388
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,750
Yes, I'm fine.

389
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,583
I really am,
you don't have to worry.

390
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:13,583
What?

391
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:14,833
[KOYUKI]
I'm just fine.

392
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:17,000
How can you say you're
fine when you had to--

393
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:19,125
Tama, where are you right now?

394
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:21,458
I'll come to you!

395
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:24,708
H-Hello? Tama?

396
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:26,208
I have to go.

397
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:31,541
[gasps]

398
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:47,833
[YUU] She's not "fine"!
I have to find her!

399
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,416
[ANNOUNCER A]
Please watch your step.

400
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,916
The doors are closing.

401
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,958
[panting]

402
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:15,500
[YUU] Back then, there was
no way for me to help her.

403
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,958
[YUU]
Even though she was hurting,

404
00:21:19,041 --> 00:21:20,916
just like she is right now.

405
00:21:34,458 --> 00:21:35,500
[YUU]
There you are!

406
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:36,500
[gasps]

407
00:21:36,583 --> 00:21:39,166
[YUU pants]

408
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:42,125
I thought I'd find you here.

409
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:43,625
What are you doing?

410
00:21:43,708 --> 00:21:45,041
I've been worried
because I don't know

411
00:21:45,125 --> 00:21:46,583
what's going on with you!

412
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:48,291
I saw the news
about your hiatus,

413
00:21:48,375 --> 00:21:50,708
and Chitose said even your
concerts are cancelled, so--

414
00:21:50,791 --> 00:21:53,083
My voice, it won't work.

415
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:55,458
Uh?

416
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:57,375
When I try singing.

417
00:21:57,458 --> 00:21:58,833
[YUU gasps]

418
00:21:58,916 --> 00:22:01,041
But it'll be okay.

419
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:04,375
I'm sure I'll be good
as new pretty soon.

420
00:22:04,458 --> 00:22:06,291
So, you don't have
to worry about me.

421
00:22:08,041 --> 00:22:10,916
And, I'm sorry my friend...

422
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:15,000
[KOYUKI]
...for loving you.

423
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:19,041
[KOYUKI]
I'm sorry...

424
00:22:53,958 --> 00:22:56,583
<i>Looking up at the sky</i>
<i>I felt an emptiness</i>

425
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:59,500
<i>All the colors of</i>
<i>summer have been faded</i>

426
00:22:59,583 --> 00:23:03,083
<i>Before I even knew the things</i>
<i>that made me the happiest</i>

427
00:23:03,166 --> 00:23:05,083
<i>Were hidden and tucked away</i>

428
00:23:05,166 --> 00:23:07,916
<i>But when I looked at you</i>
<i>it all felt so intense</i>

429
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,791
<i>Your eyes cut to the</i>
<i>core of my existence</i>

430
00:23:10,875 --> 00:23:14,250
<i>Every word that you spoke</i>
<i>was like a painting in every hue</i>

431
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:16,083
<i>You brought calm into my world</i>

432
00:23:16,166 --> 00:23:18,625
<i>All I can do now is breathe</i>

433
00:23:18,708 --> 00:23:21,583
<i>And figure out just what I need</i>

434
00:23:21,666 --> 00:23:24,208
<i>Resolve myself, pursue my dreams</i>

435
00:23:24,291 --> 00:23:26,750
<i>I'm running</i>

436
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:29,541
<i>Moving forward, taking your hand</i>

437
00:23:29,625 --> 00:23:30,916
<i>Being with you</i>

438
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,583
<i>I'm finally free enough to</i>
<i>spread out my wings</i>

439
00:23:32,666 --> 00:23:35,083
<i>Let's catch the wind</i>
<i>and go for a ride</i>

440
00:23:35,166 --> 00:23:39,000
<i>You and I can fly</i>
<i>anywhere together</i>

441
00:23:39,083 --> 00:23:41,416
<i>We can go as high</i>
<i>up as we want</i>

442
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:44,208
<i>Following the path that's</i>
<i>been laid pout before us</i>

443
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:47,791
<i>Guided by our</i>
<i>bonded hearts forever</i>

444
00:23:47,875 --> 00:23:51,208
<i>Let's keep living</i>
<i>out this fantasy</i>

445
00:23:51,291 --> 00:23:55,208
<i>And chasing our dreams</i>

446
00:23:55,291 --> 00:23:58,541
<i>Ah... Ah...</i>

447
00:23:58,625 --> 00:24:03,583
♪

448
00:24:13,791 --> 00:24:15,458
[FUUKA]
Next time, "Date!"

